> One night, while watching 2005 sleeper hit "Herbie: Fully Loaded," Chef Lindsay was hit by a wave of inspiration as intense as the moment LiLo beats Matt Dillon in that final race. (Spoiler, sorry.) "What IF! Lindsay said, What if I took the recipe for my Mom's potato chowder, added some stock concentrate for savory depth, and then topped it with enough accoutrement to stop stupid Trip in his TRACKS." And then, ladies and gentlemen, Lindsay did just that. 4 Gold Stars and all the race stripes, Chef L.

Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{5} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel,
and small dice @Yellow Onion{1}. Peel and finely chop @Garlic{1%clove}. Finely chop
@Jalapeño{1} until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings), removing ribs and seeds
if you prefer less heat.

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #medium pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add onion and garlic; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until
softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @Flour{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4); cook, stirring,
until lightly browned, ~{1%minute}.

Slowly stir in @Milk{1} a small splash at a time until fully incorporated. Stir in
@water{1 1/2%cups} (2 ½ cups for 4 servings). Add potatoes and @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}; season generously with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring
occasionally, until potatoes are very tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. (To test, pierce
one with a fork—it should go through easily!)

Meanwhile, place @Bacon{1} in a single layer in a #large pan{} over medium heat.
Cook, flipping occasionally, until crispy, ~{8-12%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer
to a #paper towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, finely chop.

Once potatoes are tender, reduce heat to low and mash to desired consistency with a
#potato masher{}. (We recommend mashing until almost smooth, with some small potato
pieces in there. Hello, texture!) Stir in half the bacon and half the @Cheddar Cheese{1}. Season generously with salt and pepper. (If mixture seems too thick, stir
in a splash of warm water.)

Divide chowder between #bowls{}; top with remaining bacon and cheddar, a dollop
of @Sour Cream{1}, and as much jalapeño as you'd like.